%% Data Flow Diagram - Llama Stack Distribution
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant LLS as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant vLLM as vLLM Server<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant FMS as FMS Guardrails<br/>Orchestrator
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Milvus as Milvus/PgVector/Qdrant<br/>Vector DB
    participant vLLMEmbed as vLLM Embedding Server<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Chat Completion (vLLM Backend)
    Client->>LLS: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP 8321/TCP<br/>Auth: Platform-managed
    LLS->>vLLM: Forward inference request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (VLLM_API_TOKEN)
    vLLM-->>LLS: Chat completion response
    LLS->>PG: Store session/state<br/>PostgreSQL 5432/TCP<br/>Auth: Username/Password
    PG-->>LLS: Ack
    LLS-->>Client: Chat completion JSON response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Safety-Guarded Inference
    Client->>LLS: POST /v1/safety/run-shield<br/>HTTP 8321/TCP<br/>Auth: Platform-managed
    LLS->>FMS: Content moderation check<br/>HTTP/HTTPS<br/>Auth: None (Optional TLS)
    FMS-->>LLS: Safety verdict
    LLS->>vLLM: Forward inference (if safe)<br/>HTTP/HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    vLLM-->>LLS: Inference response
    LLS-->>Client: Guarded response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)
    Client->>LLS: POST /v1/agents/*<br/>HTTP 8321/TCP<br/>Auth: Platform-managed
    LLS->>vLLMEmbed: Generate embeddings<br/>HTTP/HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    vLLMEmbed-->>LLS: Embedding vectors
    LLS->>Milvus: Vector similarity search<br/>gRPC/HTTP<br/>Auth: Token/Password
    Milvus-->>LLS: Relevant documents
    LLS->>vLLM: Inference with context<br/>HTTP/HTTPS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    vLLM-->>LLS: Augmented response
    LLS-->>Client: RAG response

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 4: Model Evaluation via Kubeflow
    Client->>LLS: POST /v1/eval/*<br/>HTTP 8321/TCP<br/>Auth: Platform-managed
    LLS->>KFP: Submit evaluation pipeline<br/>HTTP/HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: API Token
    KFP->>S3: Store evaluation artifacts<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP<br/>Auth: AWS Credentials
    S3-->>KFP: Ack
    KFP-->>LLS: Pipeline execution results
    LLS-->>Client: Evaluation results
